<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="419" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="419">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the pygofer with a membranous area on the dorsum and medial and ventral margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="419" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="419">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can easily be recognized by the well developed ventral apodeme and serrate lateral margin of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
